  {
    "id": "gs-10ac11c12d02",
    "title": "Physics-aware neural operator for high-fidelity fluid dynamics modeling with geometric and spectral priors",
    "authors": "X Hu, Q Ma, P Zhao, X Wang",
    "abstract": "Accurate and efficient prediction of fluid dynamics plays a critical role in aerospace engineering, energy systems, and environmental applications, where reliable flow modeling supports design optimization and reduces computational costs. Traditional computational fluid dynamics (CFD) solvers, while highly accurate, become prohibitively expensive for unsteady and multi-scale flows. Recent neural operator approaches provide an attractive alternative by learning mappings between flow states and solutions, yet their current formulations struggle to preserve physical consistency under complex geometries and often exhibit strong low-frequency bias, which limits their capability to capture essential multi-scale features in fluid dynamics. To overcome these issues, we propose a physics-aware neural operator that unifies global flow coherence modeling and local geometric consistency under a spectral balancing mechanism. Specifically, our approach captures long-range dependencies through an efficient attention-based integral representation while refining local gradients via convolutional operators, and employs adaptive normalization to mitigate low-frequency dominance. This design ensures physical consistency and accurate multi-scale feature representation without compromising efficiency. We validate the proposed approach on multiple fluid dynamics benchmarks, including canonical flow problems and complex geometry scenarios. Compared to state-of-the-art operator learning models, our method significantly reduces prediction error while maintaining strong generalization under limited training data. These results demonstrate the potential of physics-aware neural operators as an efficient and accurate alternative to traditional CFD solvers for complex fluid dynamics applications.",
