  {
    "id": "gs-685ef721d115",
    "title": "Machine learning integration in computational fluid dynamics for turbulence modeling",
    "authors": "A Naseem, S Naseem, S Fatima, N Khan",
    "abstract": "This study explores the integration of Machine Learning (ML) with Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD) to improve turbulence modeling. Key findings indicate that ML-enhanced turbulence models significantly improve accuracy and computational efficiency compared to traditional models. High-fidelity turbulence data, including Direct Numerical Simulations (DNS), enable ML models to capture the chaotic and unsteady nature of flow fields with reduced Root Mean Square Error (RMSE). Additionally, integrating ML into frameworks such as Reynolds-Averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) and Large Eddy Simulation (LES) enhances both computational speed and accuracy. Despite these advancements, challenges like overfitting, limited data accessibility, and the interpretability of black-box ML models remain. Addressing these issues is essential to fully optimize ML's potential in CFD. The study underscores the transformative impact of ML on turbulence modeling, presenting it as a pivotal tool for advancing CFD in both academic and industrial applications.",
